What would be the best method for developing new technologies for accident prevention if not imitating the obstacle sensors from nature?
For example, those of the bees.
At the CEATEC in Japan, an amazing project was presented that inspired the Nissan engineers of Hummeln in the creation of new accidents of preventive systems.
In collaboration with the Tokyo University, Nissan built the biomimetical system controlled by authorobots of the type BR23C, a mini-car equipped with the characteristics of bees, with the aim of supporting the development of a system that avoids any collisions.
